---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import DbArchitecture from '../components/DbArchitecture';
---

<Base title="Database Design" active="db-schema" section="architecture" description="Interactive schema for the podcast-factory SQLite database — 16 SOLID-compliant tables spanning the pipeline, knowledge library, and Kashkole corpus layer.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Database design</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">What the database manages and why.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-lede">
        Sixteen SOLID-compliant tables in <strong>knowledge.db</strong> replacing scattered JSONL and JSON files across pipeline books and external corpora.
        One SQLite database consolidates the knowledge store, etymology layer, corpus provenance, topic taxonomy,
        cost tracking, episode registry, and quality audit trail — everything queryable and cross-book for the first time.
        A second SQLite database, <strong>mirror.db</strong>, auto-populates from three SQL Server databases on the home network
        and powers the Source Library Server — giving the pipeline and the reader instant, zero-cost access to 6,000+ Quran verses
        and 20 years of Islamic scholarly material.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="stack">
    <DbArchitecture client:load />
  </section>

  <section class="stack design-notes">
    <h2>Design decisions</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why SQLite, not a server?</span>
        <p>
          The factory runs on a single machine. SQLite has no daemon, no config,
          no connection pooling — just a file. It handles the pipeline's write pattern
          (one book at a time, one phase at a time) without any overhead.
          The knowledge base, cost ledger, and episode registry can all be queried
          with plain <code>SELECT</code> statements from any script.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">Etymology at every scale</span>
        <p>
          Three tables form the etymology spine: <strong>arabic_roots</strong> holds
          every Semitic root with its pre-computed abjad sum; <strong>word_etymologies</strong>
          maps each root to its morphological derivations with semantic nuances and
          esoteric notes per word; <strong>letter_profiles</strong> is a static 28-row
          table that drives teaching depth at the letter level — makhraj, sifāt, solar/lunar,
          Quranic frequency, and Sufi colour correspondences. Join all three in one query.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">SOLID/DRY foundation from day one</span>
        <p>
          Four design rules are baked in. <strong>atom_sources</strong> unifies all provenance
          (pipeline books and Kashkole chapters) in one table with a <code>source_type</code>
          discriminator and a CHECK constraint — no polymorphic NULL ambiguity.
          <strong>topic_type_taxonomy</strong> replaces a hard-coded driver dict with 18 seed rows
          that the ingestion driver JOINs instead of duplicating.
          <strong>atom_topic_tags</strong> is a proper covering-indexed join table replacing
          a file-based tag index. And <code>needs_review</code> on every atom surfaces
          WARN-verdict quality signals without a separate table.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">Source library mirror — a second database (Wave J)</span>
        <p>
          <strong>mirror.db</strong> is a separate SQLite database, gitignored and under 50 MB.
          It is populated from three SQL Server databases over the local network:
          KQUR (6,236 Quran verses, Arabic roots, etymology), KASHKOLE (scholarly anthology,
          glossary, 18-type topic taxonomy), and KSESSIONS (343 lecture transcripts).
          Four FTS5 virtual tables (<code>fts_quran</code>, <code>fts_topics</code>, <code>fts_sessions</code>)
          and a unified <code>term_index</code> enable sub-millisecond lookups.
          The Source Library Server reads only mirror.db — never the SQL Server directly —
          so the pipeline stays independent of network availability after the first sync.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* ── Component root ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-root) {
    font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
  }

  /* ── Filter bar ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-filters) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }
  :global(.dba-filter-label) {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    margin-right: var(--sp-1);
  }
  :global(.dba-filter-count) {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
  }
  :global(.dba-pill) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--c-rule);
    background: transparent;
    font: 600 12px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }
  :global(.dba-pill:hover) { border-color: var(--c-ink-muted); color: var(--c-ink); }
  :global(.dba-pill--active) {
    border-color: var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent));
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent)) 8%, white);
    color: var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent));
  }
  :global(.dba-pill--clear) { border-color: var(--c-ink-muted); color: var(--c-ink-dim); }
  :global(.dba-pill-dot) {
    width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0;
    background: var(--cat-color, #87827a);
  }

  /* ── SQL table card grid ────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-grid) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }

  /* ── Individual SQL table card ──────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-sql-card) {
    border: 1.5px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    background: var(--c-bg-card);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s, opacity 0.15s;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-card:hover) {
    border-color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent));
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-card.is-selected) {
    border-color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent));
    border-width: 2px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in oklab, var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent)) 15%, transparent);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-card.is-related) {
    border-color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent));
    border-style: dashed;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-card.is-dimmed) {
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  /* Card header — colored top bar like DBeaver/pgAdmin */
  :global(.dba-sql-header) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 8px 12px 7px;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent)) 9%, var(--c-bg-card));
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent)) 22%, var(--c-rule));
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-header-left) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 7px;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-table-icon) {
    font-size: 14px;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-table-name) {
    font: 700 13px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-header-right) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-col-count) {
    font: 600 11px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    background: var(--c-bg-sunken);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
  }
  :global(.dba-wave-tag) {
    font: 700 9px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  :global(.dba-wave-tag--2) { background: rgba(0,120,212,0.1); color: #0078d4; }
  :global(.dba-wave-tag--3) { background: rgba(139,69,19,0.08); color: var(--c-accent); }

  /* Card body — the column list */
  :global(.dba-sql-body) {
    padding: 0;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-table) {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row) {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-rule-soft, rgba(31,29,24,0.06));
    transition: background 0.1s;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row:last-child) { border-bottom: none; }
  :global(.dba-sql-row:hover) {
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent)) 5%, transparent);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row.is-pk) {
    background: rgba(184,134,11,0.05);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row.is-pk:hover) {
    background: rgba(184,134,11,0.10);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-icon-cell) {
    width: 24px;
    padding: 5px 0 5px 10px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 11px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  :global(.dba-icon-col) {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--c-rule);
    vertical-align: middle;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-col-name) {
    padding: 5px 6px 5px 4px;
    font: 500 12px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink);
    width: 100%;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row.is-pk .dba-sql-col-name) {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #8b6914;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-row.is-fk .dba-sql-col-name) {
    color: #1a5a9a;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-type-cell) {
    padding: 5px 4px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-type) {
    font: 600 10px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    background: var(--c-bg-sunken);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-constraints) {
    padding: 5px 10px 5px 4px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    vertical-align: middle;
    display: flex;
    gap: 3px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  :global(.dba-con) {
    font: 700 9px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 1px 4px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }
  :global(.dba-con--pk)   { background: rgba(184,134,11,0.15); color: #8b6914; }
  :global(.dba-con--fk)   { background: rgba(26,90,154,0.10);  color: #1a5a9a; }
  :global(.dba-con--null) { background: var(--c-bg); color: var(--c-ink-muted); border: 1px dashed var(--c-rule); }

  /* Card footer */
  :global(.dba-sql-footer) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    background: var(--c-bg);
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-cat-pill) {
    font: 600 10px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-ink-muted));
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  :global(.dba-sql-expand-hint) {
    font: 400 11px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
  }

  /* ── Expanded detail drawer ─────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-drawer) {
    border: 2px solid var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent));
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    background: var(--c-bg-card);
    padding: var(--sp-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
    animation: drawer-in 0.2s ease;
  }
  @keyframes drawer-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-6px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-header) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-3);
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-title) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-table-name) {
    font: 700 18px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink);
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-close) {
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    font-size: 13px;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: background 0.1s;
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-close:hover) { background: var(--c-bg-sunken); }
  :global(.dba-badge) {
    font: 600 11px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--c-bg-sunken);
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
  }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave1) { color: var(--c-green); border-color: var(--c-green); background: rgba(74,124,74,0.07); }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave2) { color: #0078d4; border-color: #0078d4; background: rgba(0,120,212,0.07); }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave3) { color: var(--c-ink-muted); }
  :global(.dba-drawer-purpose) {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    padding: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-4);
    background: var(--c-bg);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--cat-color, var(--c-rule));
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-meta) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-meta-label) {
    font: 700 10px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }
  :global(.dba-drawer-chips) { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--sp-1); }
  :global(.dba-chip) {
    font: 600 10.5px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: none;
  }
  :global(.dba-chip--write) { background: rgba(139,69,19,0.09); color: #8b4513; }
  :global(.dba-chip--read)  { background: rgba(0,120,212,0.09); color: #0078d4; }
  :global(.dba-chip--related) {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--cat-color, var(--c-rule));
    color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-ink));
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }
  :global(.dba-chip--related:hover) { opacity: 0.75; }
  :global(.dba-chip-type) { opacity: 0.6; font-weight: 400; font-size: 10px; }
  :global(.dba-drawer-relations) { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }

  /* ── Full column detail table (in drawer) ───────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-drawer-fields-wrap) { overflow-x: auto; }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table) {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 12.5px;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table thead th) {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    background: var(--c-bg-sunken);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--c-rule);
    font: 700 10px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table tbody tr) {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(31,29,24,0.06);
    transition: background 0.1s;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table tbody tr:hover) { background: var(--c-bg); }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table tbody tr.is-pk) { background: rgba(184,134,11,0.04); }
  :global(.dba-field-detail-table tbody tr.is-pk:hover) { background: rgba(184,134,11,0.08); }
  :global(.dba-fd-icon)  { padding: 7px 6px 7px 10px; font-size: 12px; width: 24px; white-space: nowrap; }
  :global(.dba-fd-name)  {
    padding: 7px 8px;
    font: 700 12px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-fd-type)  {
    padding: 7px 8px;
    font: 600 11px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-fd-constraints) {
    padding: 7px 8px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-con--fk) {
    font: 600 10px ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace;
    padding: 1px 5px;
  }
  :global(.dba-fd-desc) {
    padding: 7px 10px 7px 8px;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 12px;
    max-width: 480px;
  }

  /* Design notes */
  .design-notes h2 { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }
  .design-notes p  { font-size: var(--fs-sm); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--c-ink-dim); margin: 0; }
  .design-notes code { font-size: 11px; background: var(--c-bg); padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
